span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">im</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- collect the elements with their negations</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finset</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">Id</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Id</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">J</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">J</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- maybe a subtype isn't the best choice for showing the group structure</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">abbrev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q₈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">//</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- satisfying the subtype hypotheses for the instance Mul.mul on Q₈</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mul_closed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- `cases hm &lt;;&gt; cases hn &lt;;&gt; ...` does not seem to be working well.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- `decide` also not panning out.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q₈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">mul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mul_closed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">val</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">prop</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">end</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">end</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">QuaternionGroupExample</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I'm leery of using a subtype here for Q₈, but not sure what else to use. I considered using an <code>inductive</code> type with tags that have a map over to the matrix values in <code>S</code> and then derive <code>Fintype</code> on it,  to appease machinery that might prefer the recursor <code>inductive</code> provides, but that seems unnecessary and clunky. I'm trying to avoid manually proving ~64 cases for closure on <code>Mul.mul</code>.  Any ideas?</p>\n<p>Oh, one other thing. In the lemma, the <code>cases hm &lt;;&gt; cases hn</code> expression is not producing flattened 64 cases  as I thought it might, instead it seems to be destructuring a (head::tail) for both <code>hm</code> and <code>hn</code>, then suggesting a recursive (strong inductive?) proof, with four cases (head_m, head_n), (head_m, tail_n), (tail_m, head_n), (tail_m, tail_n), not sure what to do with that. Maybe there is another variant of the <code>cases</code> tactic that would work better?</p>",
        "id": 508958280,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1743282526
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've seen people observe \"I^2=J^2=K^2=-Id, IJ=-JI=K, JK=-KJ=I and KI=-IK=J and now everything is obvious\".  This is only 9 things to check, and I guess the point is that everything is, up to sign, either one of these or something of the form <code>Id*X=X</code>, but I'm still not really clear on how not to have to break into 64 cases. Let me again stress my point of view that 64 is not a big number and hence it should not be hard to check 64 things. 2x2 Matrix multiplication done in the naive way is 8 multiplications and 4 additions (or it's a fun exercise to get it down to 7 multiplications) but I doubt <code>decide</code> works on complex numbers. </p>\n<p>If you were lucky enough to be at London Learning Lean yesterday you would have seen Heather Macbeth demoing her <code>normnumI</code> tactic which can do all the complex number multiplications and additions efficiently.</p>",
        "id": 508959180,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1743283323
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok then, I'll keep at it.  Looks like <code>normnumI</code> is still in the works - or at least hasn't popped up on search engines yet. Thank you for the feedback.</p>",
        "id": 508961757,
        "sender_full_name": "Derek Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1743285785
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>On this specific case, the following code will work (but takes ~10s to compile).</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">-- satisfying the subtype hypotheses for the instance Mul.mul on Q₈</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mul_closed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- `cases hm &lt;;&gt; cases hn &lt;;&gt; ...` does not seem to be working well.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- `decide` also not panning out.</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rcases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">all_goals</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">rcases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"o\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">all_goals</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
